<br>
The thing to look out for is that they are fast running.  If you're stuck using boot SoW, it takes some time to get far enough ahead of them to casty BoF.  Especially if you end up having to turn instead of running straight away.<br>
<br>
Regular Frost Giants have about 2800 hp, Savages about 3500. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aruvius>Aruvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/02 1:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TENEBROUS MOUNTAINS</span><hr size=1> Minimum Level: 29<br>
Maximum Level: 34'ish?<br>
Zone Name: Great Divide<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Tizmak Caves 1-3, Left on the wall from the waterfall.<br>
Mob List(HP) : Tizmaks of all Shapes and Sizes<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 10 I've never had a problem getting one of the three caves. One of them is almost always open.<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 4 They sometimes drop velium weapons that will sell for 3-6 plat in Shadowhaven. No coin, though.<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 6 They run fast. Will also get a caster sometimes that can ruin a quad. <br>
Faction Affected: Lowers Tizmak faction, which cannot be re-raised, but serves no useful purpose other than keeping them from aggroing you if you run by them later on in the game.<br>
<br>
Fairly good place to learn to quad as there is very little chance of getting an add unless you've hosed your coldain faction somehow by this level. You usually have to pull them down off the hill to the flatter land otherwise you get targeting issues. I use Column of Lightning and drop them in about five casts. Cave 1 has a LOT of Tizzies. You can usually pull the four at the entrance with no problem though. Cave 2 only has two spawns at the entrance so it's good, safe, steady kiting. Cave 3 has from 3-4 mobs, depending on where the runner is.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aruvius>Aruvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/02 1:26 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Minimum Level: 29<br>
Maximum Level: 36<br>
Zone Name: South Karana<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Paw Spires<br>
Mob List: Tech'Mal Gnolls<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 3 (Usually pretty camped)<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 6 (FS weapons plus 2-3 plat and change)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 2 (very easy)<br>
Faction Affected: Tech'Mal Gnolls decreased, Increases with Karana Residents, and some others.<br>
<br>
As long as you can find it open, Paw is a very easy place to kite. If you can, get the center or north spire as their are multiple pops there. If the whole of Paw is uncamped (I get lucky in offhours sometimes) then it's an xp goldmine, not to mention you can make some fairly decent cash as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astarafas>astarafas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/17/02 8:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Is it possible to stricky that? I mean, I looked for it and found it on page two !<br>
