Maximum level: 61<br>
Zone Name: Western Wastes<br>
Camp Area/Loc: Entire Zone<br>
Mob List(HP): Brontotheriums (Blue to 61, Mint to 62), Glaciar Mastodons (Blue to 61, Mint to 62)<br>
<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 4 (Mastodon Furs can be worthwhile for tailoring or selling, as can Velium Hound Furs)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7 (Rare resists, but the mobs are not social, Primarly risk is Velium Hound adds. )<br>
Faction Affected: No faction hits<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Have Run 3.  These are pretty much your last hurrah at quadding in pre-pop zones.   The mobs are not social, so if you are resist or crit too much of a difference in HP some will turn while the others still chase you.  You can generally just make a loop until the unturned mob or mobs join back in (they have insane regen) and then nuke them all turned at once.<br>
<br>
Velium hounds are harder to spot, but if you see several of them up there is no reason they would not be quaddable similarly.<br>
<br>
If you get a velium hound add and you are not sowed, it WILL be faster than you.  Run far enough that your quad does not beat on you (4 of these mobs hitting you is unpleasant briefly), then root and snare the dog.  Abandon quad if necessary, but unless you are marginal on mana, it should not really be necessary.   If you are sowed you can outrun the dog, but they are fast enough that you will have to generate a lot of distance from your quad to do so.  Better generally to take the hits and root/snare them, kill them, and resume your quad.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charr@graffeswizardcompilation>Charr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/8/03 5:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dragon Necropolis</span><hr size=1> Minimum Level: 60<br>
Maximum Level: 61<br>
Zone Name: Dragon Necropolis<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Zone In<br>
Mob List(HP) : Phase Spiders (Blue to 61, Mint to 62)<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 - Generally available<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 4 Sometimes drop Phase Spider Blood (nice for non casters) and about every 30th one or so drops a PSC.<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 10 I don't generally quad these intentionally, I go for 2 or 3, and if I get an add, snare it and quad then.   They run fast, hit hard,  proc yonder on you, spring from traps, warp on you, warp unexpectedly in front of you while pulling others, etc.   Learn where the traps are so you can pop and pull them.<br>
Faction Affected: None<br>
<br>
Notes<br>
-----<br>
Pull with Atol's.  You need the time on the snare and the resist bonus and you don't want them after you at full speed.<br>
<br>
Pop traps invised, swarming beatles see invis though so avoid that trap (second ramp corner)<br>
<br>
When a spider hits you that you weren't expecting, cast Atol's on it while it is hitting you.  Their melee range is such that they will start hitting you while you are still out of the range of Atol's.  I've only hit myself with snare once doing this and I was dealing with multiple spiders at the time (/hug exodus)<br>
<br>
The spiders proc a phase shift (Yonder) on you.  This can be disorienting.  If you get confused, bail and try again.   If you get ported mid-cast duck immediately and recast.  Getting phase shifted is counted as a (long) movement so your cast is already blown.  You can also get ported onto the bones which hold Dragon Construct traps.  Dragon Constructs stay up for days and like any dragonish thing, require melee range to cast on making them essentially unkillable by you solo.<br>
<br>
The spiders are fairly resistant so you may have to snare several times.  This can be problematic with a full quad when you keep seeing one or two resist messages.  <br>
<br>
Even snared these things are fast.   Run the lot of them back to the zone in and in a big loop around it as you burn.<br>
<br>
Pathing when you pull is fubar (particularly past the first ramp) so watch and make sure they are following, you may have to back track a bit. <p>&lt;br&gt;Sorcerer of Anlah'Shok&lt;br&gt;Erolissi Marr&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162304 &quot;&gt;[Magelo Profile]&lt;/a&gt;<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=palis>Palis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/13/03 3:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> might want to consolidate this with the thread above it <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32024">Master Palis Rahl</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Sorcerer of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://farsight.kicks-ass.net"> Farsight</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tethaxfirestorm>Tethax Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/13/03 1:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> in re: drakes of cobalt scar -<br>
